# ===========================
# Restic Include File (macOS)
# Example template — bootstrap.sh replaces {{HOME}} with your home directory.
# ===========================
# Strategy:
# - Back up all personal data under {{HOME}}.
# - Keep key system/dev configs that are hard to recreate.
# - Let the exclude file trim out caches, trash, and rebuildable artifacts.

# --- Core user data (everything lives here) ---
{{HOME}}

# --- Global/system config that may be useful to keep ---
# System-wide config files (network, services, etc. - small but valuable)
/etc

# Homebrew configs (Apple Silicon)
/opt/homebrew/etc

# (Intel Mac Homebrew configs – harmless on Apple Silicon; ignore if unused)
# /usr/local/etc

# --- Shared user data (optional but usually small) ---
/Users/Shared

# --- Optional: specific “must not lose” dirs (redundant but explicit) ---
# Uncomment if you want to be extra explicit; they are already under {{HOME}}
# {{HOME}}/Documents
# {{HOME}}/Desktop
# {{HOME}}/Pictures
# {{HOME}}/Music
# {{HOME}}/Movies
# {{HOME}}/Git
# {{HOME}}/.ssh
# {{HOME}}/.config
